Its appears in various forms , such as in hard amalgamated crystals like ice cubes , or loosely accumulated granules like in snow . This causes the repelling nature of like-like charges to overcome the forces of attraction in the structure , causing ice to exhibit the unusual characteristic of becoming less dense as it cools , where conventional wisdom declares that the lower the temperature the denser a matter becomes .
